## 1. Context & Background
Bitcoin adoption in West Africa (specifically Benin) is rising, but merchants face two hurdles: **Volatility** and **Technical Trust**. **SpendSat** is the first internal product of **Citrusrate**, designed to leverage our proprietary price-aggregator API to make Bitcoin spending as simple as a cash transaction for local snack vendors and businesses.

## 2. Goals & Objectives
* **Company Goal:** Validate the Citrusrate API in a real-world retail environment.
* **Product Goal:** Enable instant XOF-to-Sats conversion for point-of-sale transactions.
* **Success Metric:** Zero manual calculation errors by the merchant during checkout.

## 3. User Problem Statements
* "As a merchant, I don't know how many Sats to ask for a 500 FCFA yogurt."
* "As a customer, I want to pay with Lightning but I'm afraid of being overcharged due to volatility."

## 4. Features & Functional Specs (The Catalog)
The system must handle a diversified inventory. Below is the reference data for the MVP:

| Item Name | Category | Net Weight/Vol | Unit | Base Price (XOF) | Priority |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Yogurt Drink | Dairy | 200 | ml | 500 | P0 (Must) |
| Mini Donuts | Bakery | 250 | g | 1000 | P0 (Must) |
| Savory Pastries | Bakery | 120 | g | 500 | P0 (Must) |
| Raw Cocoa | Raw Material | 1 | kg | 8000 | P1 (Should) |
| Refined Sugar | Raw Material | 5 | kg | 4500 | P1 (Should) |

* **Logic:** The app must fetch the BTC/XOF rate from **Citrusrate API** every 60 seconds.

## 5. Requirements & Constraints
* **UX/Ergonomics:** The "Pay" button must always display the total in **Sats** clearly.
* **Performance:** Lightning Invoice generation must take less than 3 seconds.
* **Constraint:** The app requires an active internet connection to ping the Citrusrate API.

## 6. User Stories
* **Story 1:** "A customer buys 2 yogurts. The merchant taps '+' twice. The app calls Citrusrate API and shows 1000 XOF = [X] Sats. A QR code is generated."
* **Story 2:** "A merchant wants to sell 1kg of Cocoa. They select 'kg' as the unit, and the price updates to 8000 XOF converted to Sats."

## 7. Out of Scope (What we are NOT building yet)
* ❌ Multi-currency support (Only XOF for now).
* ❌ Fiat-to-Bank withdrawal (Bitcoin stays in the Lightning Wallet).
* ❌ Advanced Inventory Management (No low-stock alerts yet).

## 8. Glossary
* **Sats:** Satoshis (1/100,000,000 of a Bitcoin).
* **XOF:** West African CFA Franc.
* **Citrusrate API:** Our internal engine for real-time African currency conversion.
